						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Sivak wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If a point enters a solid surface, you are pushed to the side.  But what if you jump and the surface is above you?  The point would enter a solid surface and you'd get pushed aside instead of down because the point is in a solid surface.</div>
<br />This can easily be solved by handling vertical and horizontal motion separately, like I said before. First move horizontally, check for walls, eject horizontally if necessary. Then move vertically, check for floor/ceiling, eject vertically if necessary. If you move in both axis at once and check for collisions later it really will be hard to find a good solution.</div>

