				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">OK, I have just foreseen an issue with this method....  If you jump AND move right (or fall too), then the top right point could conceivably be inside a solid surface and you'd be ejected to the left accordingly...  
<br />
<br />I guess it'd seem to me one would have to do something along these lines for handling collision detections:
<br />
<br />-If right, check both top right and lower right points.
<br />-If up, check both top right and top left points.
<br />-If up and right, first check lower right for ejection to the left, then the 2 top points???  Although if you are above a block and your top right point is hitting a wall, but the lower right is not, then what?
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;XXXX<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XXXX<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;XXXX<br />PPP*XXX<br />PPPP<br />PPPP<br />PPPP<br />;I'm jumping and my top right point is in a block...&nbsp; what would happen?<br /></div></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-Sivak
